<dl id="n53123k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53123k">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53123k"> 123(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> his / Khantaka horse, Chandaka <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53123k"><li>FW 24.23 </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/lexa.htm#n53123k">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/l39a.htm#n53123k">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53123k">MS BL 47476a-149</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:321 <a name="ad7" href="../../ff/fdra/ada.htm#ad7">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/a/ad7.htm#n53123k">Draft: I.1&sect;1.7</a>/2.7</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Il appela son &eacute;cuyer, le rapide <mark>Chandaka</mark>: <p>&laquo;Am&egrave;ne-moi tout de suite, dit-il, <mark>mon cheval Kanthaka</mark>. Je veux partir d&apos;ici pour aller vers l&apos;&eacute;ternelle b&eacute;atitude.&raquo;</p> <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 57</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Having decided on a life of monasticism, Siddharta summoned his squire Chandaka and told him to make ready his favourite horse Kanthaka. </mm> </dd></dl>
